I. Core Philosophy: The Chronomos Coherence Engine (CCE)

The CCE is a paradigm shift designed to eliminate systemic risk stemming
from information latency and non-repudiation gaps. It operates on two
foundational, self-securing mandates that transcend traditional security
and governance models.
Mandate 1: Zero-Latency Aversion (ZDAV)

   - *Goal:* To detect and neutralize threats in real-time, enforcing
   security policy injection (G-SHIELD) before damage can occur.
   - *Mechanism:* G-NEXUS uses the Aether Sentinel (LLM) for *Structured
   Command Execution (SCE)*, translating complex data streams into
   immediate, machine-executable policy responses.

Mandate 2: Simplicity of Immutable Mandates (SIM)

   - *Goal:* To establish an unimpeachable *Immutable Chain of Custody
   (ICC)* for all sensitive actions and data.
   - *Mechanism:* The *ULTRA-STRANG* architecture embeds all transactions,
   communications, and archival events within the Hyper-Temporal Ledger
   (Firestore), ensuring non-repudiation and audibility.

II. Technical Architecture & Artifacts

The CCE is deployed via the *Aether Agent Executive Tier Utility Console*,
a single-file, full-stack application demonstrating Mandate enforcement.

